{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1444305988,"nonce":"ueJK2QY0VUljnWFGZN3h1zODxkA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMTA0MzQ1NTk=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/304","origin":"github"},"title":"Include cairo in package_r_* or not?","message":"Currently package_r_3_2_1 depends on package_cairo_1_12_14, because cairo-support is explicitly compiled into R (./configure --with-cairo). This specific version of cairo does not compile on gcc-4.9 (see Issue #294 ). Cairo can however be dynamically loaded into a R version that was compiled without cairo support. \nShould we therefore abandon compiling in cairo into R? This should give us more flexibility of which cairo version we would like to install into R.\nA quick search among tools-iuc tools suggests that currently this would affect only vegan, which should be changed to explicitly depend on cairo.\nThe alternative is to switch R_3_2_1 (and older versions) to depend on cairo-1.14.2.\nWhat do you think, @yhoogstrate @bgruening ?","files":null}]}